HEADWORD: Supraclavicle
<hw>Su`pra*clav"i*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A bone which usually connects the clavicle with
the post-temporal in the pectorial arch of fishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supraclavicular</ent>⟦br⟧
